# --- Generated output (from chord_diagram.py's CLI mode) ---
# Running `python3 chord_diagram.py` directly writes its output into
# the current working directory: per-chord/scale LilyPond source,
# the combined wrapper, the final PDF, and every keyboard/fretboard/
# chart image (both PDF and SVG). None of that belongs in version
# control -- it's regenerated from the spelling you type in each run.
#
# Anchored to the repo root (leading /) rather than a blanket *.pdf,
# so a deliberately-committed example PDF/SVG -- e.g. in an examples/
# folder for the README -- isn't swept up by this rule. Only output
# dropped straight in the root, where the CLI actually writes it, gets
# ignored.
/*.ly
/*.lytex
/*.tex
/*.pdf
/*.svg
/lilypond-book-out/

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/

# --- OS / editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
